line_2: For you, if you think well.

line_1: Where he boasts of his conquest to Susan and Nell:
line_2: And at noon he goes flaunting all over the vale,

line_1: Says he, there's little merry Nell,
line_2: I think I like her very well;

line_1: How capricious were Nature and Art to poor Nell?
line_2: She was painting her Cheeks at the time her Nose fell.
